  "description": "I write more on my website than I do here. Most recently I\u0026rsquo;ve been babbling around implementing Moscow-school semiosis in LISP to better map the different sciences and schools I use in my research.\nThis first link looks at the modern shape of the minimal claims of what a science is\nBabble, [2025-09-16 Tue 18:25]\nI reach the conclusion that it seems functionally equivalent to Moscow-school semiotics, specifically Lotman\u0026rsquo;s.\nSo in this second link, I start to sketch out what encoding Lotman\u0026rsquo;s semiosis in in LISP would look like, so I can (down the line) see if I can encode some sciences and scientific texts.\n",
